217 U.S. 594

30 S.Ct. 694

54 L.Ed. 896

H. J. SCHULTZ et al., Appellants,
v.
EDGAR B. DIEHL and Daniel Grabill.

No. 166.

Supreme Court of the United States

April 25, 1910

Mr. Charles W. Fulton for appellants.

No appearance for appellees.

Per Curiam:

1

Decree reversed, with costs, and cause remanded, to be proceeded in according to law. Jellenik v. Huron Copper Min. Co. 177 U. S. 1, 44 L. ed. 647, 20 Sup. Ct. Rep. 559; 18 Stat. at L. 470, chap. 137, § 8, U. S. Comp. Stat. 1901, p. 513; Oregon Code, §§ 5064, 300, 301.
